The newly-appointed Director of Public Relations and Information (DOPRI), Nigerian Air Force, NAF, Air Commodore Wapkerem Maigida, on Friday, resumed duty following the recent posting and redeployment by the service. In his address, Maigida promised that the directorate would work with the media in repositioning the Nigerian Air Force. “Let me assure you that the directorate will progress under my watch to continue to churn out and leverage online media platforms to bring out NAF stories in a clear picture. “To galvanise support and goodwill for the NAF in striving to project air power to overcome the myriads of security challenges currently bedevilling the country.”